%% seq_05_org_invite.mmd
%% Scope: Organization invitation, direct-add, and role management
%% Backend refs:
%%   - POST /organizations/:id/members/invite → InviteMemberController → InviteUserCommand
%%   - POST /organizations/:id/members/add → AddMemberController → AddMemberCommand
%%   - POST /organizations/:id/members/add-direct → AddDirectMemberController
%%   - POST /organizations/:id/members/update-role/:userId → UpdateMemberRoleController
%%   - DELETE /organizations/:id/members/:userId → RemoveMemberController
%%   - GET /organizations/:id/members/ → ListMembersController
%%   - ⚠️ AcceptInvitationCommand does NOT exist (invitation accept is NOT implemented)
%%   - ⚠️ No email sending — invitation creates record only
%%   - ⚠️ Transmit transport=null (no WebSocket)

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Admin as Org Owner/Admin
    participant B as Browser (Svelte)
    participant C as Controller
    participant Cmd as Command
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    actor User as Target User

    Note over Admin, User: === INVITE MEMBER ===
    Note over C: InviteMemberController

    Admin->>B: Enter user to invite
    B->>C: POST /organizations/:id/members/invite
    C->>Cmd: InviteUserCommand.execute(dto)
    Cmd->>DB: INSERT INTO organization_invitations
    (organization_id, invited_email,
    invitation_token, expires_at = 7 days,
    invited_by)
    DB-->>Cmd: Invitation created
    Note over Cmd: ⚠️ No email sent
    Note over Cmd: ⚠️ AcceptInvitationCommand
    Note over Cmd: does NOT exist —
    Note over Cmd: invitation flow is INCOMPLETE
    Cmd-->>C: Invitation object
    C-->>B: Redirect back

    Note over Admin, User: === DIRECT ADD MEMBER ===
    Note over C: AddMemberCommand (bypasses invitation)

    Admin->>B: Add member directly
    B->>C: POST /organizations/:id/members/add
    C->>Cmd: AddMemberCommand.execute(dto)
    Cmd->>DB: Check user exists
    Cmd->>DB: Check not already member
    Cmd->>DB: INSERT INTO organization_users
    (organization_id, user_id,
    org_role='org_member',
    status='approved',
    invited_by=admin.id)
    Cmd-->>C: Member added
    C-->>B: Redirect back

    Note over Admin, User: === LIST MEMBERS ===
    Note over C: ListMembersController

    Admin->>B: Open member page
    B->>C: GET /organizations/:id/members/
    C->>DB: SELECT ou.*, u.*
    FROM organization_users ou
    JOIN users u ...
    WHERE status='approved'
    C-->>B: Member list
    B-->>Admin: Show members with roles

    Note over Admin, User: === CHANGE ROLE ===
    Note over C: UpdateMemberRoleController

    Admin->>B: Change member role
    B->>C: POST /organizations/:id/members/update-role/:userId
    C->>Cmd: UpdateMemberRoleCommand.execute(dto)
    Cmd->>Cmd: Permission check
    (only org_owner/org_admin can change)
    Cmd->>DB: UPDATE organization_users
    SET org_role = ? WHERE user_id = ?
    Cmd-->>C: OK
    C-->>B: Redirect back

    Note over Admin, User: === REMOVE MEMBER ===
    Note over C: RemoveMemberController

    Admin->>B: Remove member
    B->>C: DELETE /organizations/:id/members/:userId
    C->>Cmd: RemoveMemberCommand.execute(dto)
    Cmd->>Cmd: Check not last owner
    Cmd->>DB: DELETE FROM organization_users
    WHERE user_id = ? AND organization_id = ?
    Cmd-->>C: OK
    C-->>B: Redirect back


